[Mind Counter] Privacy Policy

This app does not collect, store, or share personal information from users.

1. Data Collection
The app does not collect personally identifiable information such as name, email address, or contact details.
The app may process user-input data (such as counting targets or activity records), which may be considered health-related information. However, this data is stored and processed only locally on the user's device and is never transmitted to any server or third party.

2. Technical Data
The app may collect limited technical information (such as device type or error logs) strictly for the purpose of maintaining app functionality. This information does not identify users personally.

3. Data Storage and Retention
All user data is stored locally on the user's device. The app does not store data on external servers.
Data is retained only until the user deletes the app or clears the app data.

4. Data Deletion
Users can delete their data at any time by uninstalling the app or clearing app storage through device settings.

5. Data Sharing
The app does not share any user data with third parties.

6. Policy Changes
This privacy policy may be updated in the future. Any changes will be reflected within the app.

